$ PowerShell: function statement

The `function` statement creates → Windows/PowerShell/language/function[functions].

{ Show definition of function

 gh|about-powershell|/language/statement/function/show-definition.ps1||

}

sa:

  → Windows/PowerShell/language/statement/function/parameters[Function parameters]

  A function's → Windows/PowerShell/language/function/begin-process-end-block[`begin`, `process` and `end` block]

  → Windows/PowerShell/language/statement[Others statements]

  The → Windows/PowerShell/language/variable/automatic[automatic] variable → Windows/PowerShell/language/variable/automatic/PsCmdLet[`$psCmdlet`] and
  the → Windows/PowerShell/language/variable/preference[preference] variable → Windows/PowerShell/language/variable/preference/MaximumFunctionCount[`$maximumFunctionCount`].

  A function is an → Windows/PowerShell/language/item[item] that is exposed through the *function* → Windows/PowerShell/language/provider[provider].
